---
import Layout from '../components/Layout.astro'
import '../styles/global.css'
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — tinytime"
  description="Privacy policy for tinytime, including Google Calendar read-only integration handling."
  path="/privacy"
>
  <section class="py-16">
    <div class="tiny-container max-w-3xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-[var(--tiny-muted)]">Last updated: April 23, 2026</p>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-sm leading-7 text-[var(--tiny-fg)]">
        <p>
          tinytime is operated by Mehran Bolhasani. For privacy questions or data requests, contact
          <a class="tiny-link" href="mailto:privacy@tinytime.work">privacy@tinytime.work</a>.
        </p>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Data we collect</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-[var(--tiny-muted)]">
            <li>Account data: email address and auth identifiers.</li>
            <li>App data: projects, tags, and time entries you create.</li>
            <li>Google integration data: OAuth tokens and selected calendar IDs.</li>
            <li>Read-only Google Calendar events for the connected account when requested by you.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">How data is used</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--tiny-muted)]">
            Data is used only to provide core app features. Google Calendar data is used only to show
            read-only calendar events in tinytime's calendar day view.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Storage and retention</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--tiny-muted)]">
            Data is stored in Supabase infrastructure. Google OAuth tokens are stored for connected
            integrations until you disconnect your account or request deletion. Calendar events are
            fetched on demand and are not permanently stored for unrelated processing.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Sharing</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--tiny-muted)]">
            tinytime does not sell personal data and does not share Google user data with third parties
            except as necessary to provide the service and comply with legal obligations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Your controls</h2>
          <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-[var(--tiny-muted)]">
            <li>Disconnect Google access from tinytime settings.</li>
            <li>Revoke tinytime access from your Google account security settings.</li>
            <li>Request account and data deletion by emailing privacy@tinytime.work.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold">Google API Services User Data Policy</h2>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--tiny-muted)]">
            tinytime's use and transfer of information received from Google APIs adheres to the
            <a class="tiny-link" href="https://developers.google.com/terms/api-services-user-data-policy" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">
              Google API Services User Data Policy
            </a>
            , including the Limited Use requirements.
          </p>
          <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--tiny-muted)]">
            tinytime only uses access to read-only Google Calendar data to provide user-visible calendar
            overlay functionality inside the app. This data is never used for advertising, sold to data
            brokers, or used to train generalized AI or machine learning models.
          </p>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
